import contextily as ctx
manzana = "C:/.../Capas_Atlampa/Infoxmanzana/Infoxmanzana_Atlampa.shp"
map_data = gpd.read_file(manzana)

from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

map_data = map_data.to_crs(epsg=3395) #WGS84 Mercator

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 10))

# Control del título y los ejes
ax.set_title('Población total por manzanas', pad = 20, fontdict={'fontsize':20, 'color': '#4873ab'})

divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)

cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.1)

ax=map_data.plot(column='pobtot_n', ax=ax, legend=True, cax=cax)

# contextily
#mp = map_data.plot(column = 'pobtot_n', figsize=(9, 9), alpha=0.5, color='grey');
ctx.add_basemap(ax, source=ctx.providers.Stamen.TonerLite)

In [204]:
map_data = map_data.fillna(0)
data_1=map_data['pisodt_n'].astype(np.int64)
data_2 =map_data['elec_n'].astype(np.int64)
data_3 =map_data['aguadv_n'].astype(np.int64)
data_4 =map_data['drenaj_n'].astype(np.int64)
data_5 =map_data['excusa_n'].astype(np.int64)

data = [data_1, data_2, data_3, data_4, data_5 ] 
  
fig = plt.figure(figsize =(10, 7)) 
ax = fig.add_subplot(111) 
  
# Creating axes instance 
bp = ax.boxplot(data, patch_artist = True, 
                notch ='True', vert = 0) 
  
colors = ['#fdd0a2', '#ffffbf',  
          '#6baed6', '#df65b0', '#67000d'] 
  
for patch, color in zip(bp['boxes'], colors): 
    patch.set_facecolor(color)  
# changing color and linewidth of 
# whiskers 
for whisker in bp['whiskers']: 
    whisker.set(color ='#8B008B',  
                linewidth = 1.5, 
                linestyle =":") 
# changing color and linewidth of 
# caps 
for cap in bp['caps']: 
    cap.set(color ='#8B008B', 
            linewidth = 2) 
# changing color and linewidth of 
# medians 
for median in bp['medians']: 
    median.set(color ='red', 
               linewidth = 3) 

# changing style of fliers 
for flier in bp['fliers']: 
    flier.set(marker ='D', 
              color ='#e7298a', 
              alpha = 0.5) 
      
# x-axis labels 
ax.set_yticklabels(['Recubrimiento en piso', 'Energía eléctrica',  
                    'Agua potable','Drenaje','Servicio sanitario']) 
  
# Adding title  
plt.title("Servicios disponibles en viviendas por manzana") 
  
# Removing top axes and right axes 
# ticks 
ax.get_xaxis().tick_bottom() 
ax.get_yaxis().tick_left() 
      
# show plot 
plt.show(bp)
